constructor.details: Instantiate the kernel with executor and admin addresses.

params._admin: Address in charge of granting and revoking roles.
params._executor: Address in charge of handling kernel executions.

executeAction(uint8,address).details: Executes an action on a target address.

params.target_: Address upon which the action will operate.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants a role to the target address.

params.addr_: Address that will receive the role.
params.role_: Role to grant to the target.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes a role from the target address.

params.addr_: Address that will have the role removed.
params.role_: Role to revoke from the target.
